		{ ref: `Romans 8:15`, slug: `romans`, ch: 8, text: `You did not receive a spirit of slavery to fall back into fear; you received the Spirit of adoption, by whom you cry out, "Abba, Father."`, note: `Faith was never meant to be lived in fear. The Spirit teaches you to call God "Abba" — Father, the most tender name.` },
		{ ref: `John 1:12`, slug: `john`, ch: 1, text: `But to all who received Him, who believed in His name, He gave the right to become children of God — children of the Father.`, note: `Being His child is a right He gives, a gift you receive — not a status you achieve.` },
		{ ref: `Galatians 4:6`, slug: `galatians`, ch: 4, text: `Because you are His children, God sent the Spirit of His Son into your hearts, the Spirit who calls out, "Abba, Father."`, note: `God Himself put the cry "Father" inside you. That longing for closeness is His own Spirit at work.` },
		{ ref: `Matthew 6:9`, slug: `matthew`, ch: 6, text: `Pray then like this: Our Father in heaven, hallowed be Your name.`, note: `The prayer you have prayed all your life begins with the truth of everything — He is your Father.` },
