	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; George MacDonald, Charles Spurgeon, and Andrew Murray (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You may not feel everything shift the first time you read. That is okay. The Father's love is not a passing feeling — it is a foundation, and foundations are laid quietly, one day at a time. Every passage you take in is your Father planting an assurance in you that guilt and distance cannot uproot.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"My child, you have served Me, prayed to Me, and kept faith through many seasons — and I have seen every one. But I never asked you to earn My love, and you cannot lose it by falling short. You do not have to appease Me or win back what was never withdrawn. I am not standing far off, keeping score. I am the Father who watches the road for you.</p><p>So come home to Me, just as you are. While you are still a long way off, I am already running to you. You are not a servant hoping to be accepted — you are My beloved son, My beloved daughter, by grace, right now. Rest in that. I delight in you, and nothing you have done or left undone can change whose you are."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for Catholics`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, who art in heaven, we come to You in the name of Your Son. We thank You for the faith handed down through the centuries — for Christ, for Your Church, for the prayer You taught us to pray. And we ask, gently, for something deeper still: that every Catholic heart would know You not only as Lord and Judge, but as the near and tender Father You truly are.</p><p>For all who carry the quiet weight of trying to earn Your favor, let them hear that Your love is a gift of grace, lavished and not measured. For all who feel distant from You, run to meet them as the father ran to his returning son. Lift the burden of guilt and fear, and put in its place the Spirit of adoption, that they would cry out to You, "Abba, Father," and know they are fully accepted as Your own children.</p><p>Open Your Word to them in their own language. Give them assurance that in Christ there is no condemnation, and that nothing can separate them from Your love. Draw them into a living friendship with You — from recited prayer into real conversation, from obligation into delight.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
