	faqs={[
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about God as Father?`, answer: `Scripture reveals God as a loving Father from beginning to end. Jesus taught us to pray "Our Father in heaven" (Matthew 6:9), and Romans 8:15 says we received the Spirit of adoption by whom we cry "Abba, Father." 1 John 3:1 marvels at the great love the Father has lavished on us, that we should be called His children. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as Father wherever Scripture does — read and hear it free at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Are there good Bible verses for Catholics?`, answer: `Yes — verses your own faith already treasures. Luke 15:20 (the father runs to his returning son), Matthew 6:9 (Our Father in heaven), Romans 8:15 and Galatians 4:6 (the Spirit who cries "Abba, Father"), 1 John 3:1 (the love the Father has lavished on us), and Ephesians 2:8-9 (saved by grace) all speak to the heart of the gospel. Read and listen to them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Does God love me even when I fail or fall short?`, answer: `Yes. Romans 8:1 says there is now no condemnation for those who are in Christ, and Luke 15 shows the father running to embrace a son who had failed badly — before the son could finish his apology. God's love is not a wage you earn or a favor you maintain; it is grace He gives. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you meet a Father who runs to meet you, not a judge keeping score.` },
		{ question: `What does it mean to be saved by grace and not by works?`, answer: `Ephesians 2:8-9 says it plainly: "by grace you have been saved, through faith — and this is not from yourselves, it is the gift of God — not by works, so that no one can boast." Your devotion and good works are a beautiful response to God's love, but they are not the price of it. You are accepted as His beloved child by grace. Read the passage free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `How can I have assurance of God's love?`, answer: `Assurance grows as you hear what God Himself says. 1 John 3:1 says we are children of God — "and that is what we are." Romans 8:38-39 says nothing can separate you from His love, and Romans 8:15 says you received a Spirit of adoption, not of fear. The Father's Heart Bible™ lets you read and listen to these promises directly, so the Father's own voice can settle the question for you at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free Bible with audio I can read on my own?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on your phone and read or hear any book — ideal for a quiet hour, your commute, or time before Mass. The Church has always invited the faithful to encounter God in His Word, and here it is in plain English.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different?`, answer: `It is a fresh English translation that reveals God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so the nearness many faithful Catholics long for meets them right on the page. It is written with deep respect for the Christian heritage, and it points readers to the heart of the gospel: that by grace you are already God's beloved child, welcomed by a Father who runs to meet you.` },
